data.description: Such a lovely Midtown BRICK home! Located in the beautiful Leinkauf Historic District in the center of the city! The home has 2 bedrooms & 2 baths and is 1831 square feet. You'll have 2 properties on one lot! The back house is brick also and is 600 sf and has a kitchen, living room, bedroom & bath. Southern charm abounds on this wonderful old street! Flo Claire is one of Mobile's oldest subdivisions and this lovely home features hardwood flooring, the original front door, fireplace, french doors, and many more of its original charming features. Over the past few years there have been several updates to the home. The kitchen has beautiful granite countertops, split brick floors, and a Jenn-Air range. You'll be near grocery stores, restaurants, parks, shops, and downtown! Hurry over and make this unique property your HOME SWEET HOME! This home needs just a few improvements like paint, and some sheetrock repair in one bedroom. The back house needs a good deep cleaning as the previous occupant did smoke. New HVAC may need to be installed also. This property has been priced with all this in mind. Home being sold as-is, where is, and seller will not be doing any repairs. Any furniture in the home or on back patio will remain. No sellers disclosure will be provided because the family member who is handling this sale has never lived in home. Motivated Seller!
